Students learn and analyze various methods of teaching French language and different techiques to develop listening, speaking, reading and writing skills. They learn to analyze and to use different textbooks and various models of organizing a French language course. Students get an overview of the present situation of teaching French in Estinia, with the French language curricula and the principles of the State Exam in French. The work is held in the form of individual and team work during the seminarsObjectives/eesmärkid:  Learning and analyzing different French language teaching methodologiesLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student has an overview of the main methods of French language teaching and the techniques applied in various methodologies to develop different skills; is able to analyze French textbooks  from a methodological viewpoint and to apply them in course; has an overview of the situation of teaching French language in Estonia, the French language curricula on different levels and the principles of state exams in French.
